{"title_page": "List of cities in China by population", "text_new": "{{Short description|Wikimedia list article}}\n\nChina is the [[list of countries and dependencies by population|world's most populous country]]. According to the Demographic research group in 2017, there are 102 Chinese cities with over 1 million people in the \"urban area\", as defined by the group's methodology.<ref name=\"demographia\">{{cite news|title=More than 100 Chinese cities now above 1 million people|url=https://www.theguardian.com/cities/2017/mar/20/china-100-cities-populations-bigger-liverpool|publisher=Guardian|date=March 20, 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Definition and classification==\nAccording to the [[administrative divisions of China]], there are three levels of cities, namely [[direct-administered municipalities of China|direct-administered municipalities]] ({{lang|zh-hans|\u76f4\u8f96\u5e02}}), [[prefecture-level city|prefecture-level cities]] ({{lang|zh-hans|\u5730\u7ea7\u5e02}}), and [[county-level city|county-level cities]] ({{lang|zh-hans|\u53bf\u7ea7\u5e02}}). The [[special administrative regions of China|Special Administrative Regions]] ({{lang|zh-hans|\u7279\u522b\u884c\u653f\u533a}}) of [[Hong Kong]] and [[Macau]] and the [[free area of the Republic of China|areas controlled]] by the [[Taiwan|Republic of China (Taiwan)]] are not included in this administrative classification.\n\nMunicipalities and prefecture-level cities are not each a \"city\" in the strictest sense of the term, but instead an administrative unit comprising, typically, both an urban core (''a city in the strict sense'') and surrounding [[rural area|rural]] or less-urbanized areas usually many times the size of the central, built-up core.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Zhang|first=L.|last2=Zhao|first2=Simon X. B.|date=June 1998|title=Re-examining China's \u201cUrban\u201d Concept and the Level of Urbanization|journal=The China Quarterly|language=en|volume=154|pages=330\u2013381|doi=10.1017/S030574100000206X}}</ref>\n\nPrefecture-level cities nearly always contain multiple [[counties of China|counties]] ({{lang|zh-hans|\u53bf}}), [[county-level city|county-level cities]], and other such sub-divisions. To distinguish a prefecture-level city from its actual urban area (''city in the strict sense''), the term \"{{lang|zh-hans|\u5e02\u533a}}\" (''sh\u00ec q\u016b''; \"urban area\") is used. However, even this term often encompasses large suburban regions often greater than {{convert|1000|sqmi|km2|-3}}, sometimes only the urban core whereas the agglomeration overtake the city limits. Thus, the \"urban core\" would be roughly comparable to the American term \"city limit\", the \"sh\u00ec q\u016b or urban area\" would be roughly comparable to \"metropolitan area\", and the municipality is a political designation defining regions under control of a municipal government, which has no comparable designation.{{Citation needed|date=June 2019}}\n\n== List of major cities by population ==\nThe list contains all the cities with the administrative designation of \"[[National Central City]]\" ({{lang|zh-hans|\u56fd\u5bb6\u4e2d\u5fc3\u57ce\u5e02}}) and \"[[Sub-provincial division#Sub-provincial municipalities|Sub-Provincial City]]\" ({{lang|zh-hans|\u526f\u7701\u7ea7\u57ce\u5e02}}) \u2013 including five \"[[List of capitals in China#List of the Municipalities with Independent Planning Status|Municipalities with Independent Planning Status]]\" ({{lang|zh-hans|\u8ba1\u5212\u5355\u5217\u5e02}}) and ten large \"[[list of capitals in China|Provincial Capital Cities]]\" ({{lang|zh-hans|\u7701\u4f1a\u57ce\u5e02}}), as well as some large \"[[special economic zones of China|Special Economic Zones]]\" ({{lang|zh-hans|\u7ecf\u6d4e\u7279\u533a\u57ce\u5e02}}), \"[[Special economic zones of China#List of the SEZs and Open Coastal Cities|Open Coastal Cities]]\" ({{lang|zh-hans|\u6cbf\u6d77\u5f00\u653e\u57ce\u5e02}}) and \"[[prefecture-level city|Prefecture-Level Cities]]\" ({{lang|zh-hans|\u5730\u7ea7\u5e02}}).<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.citypopulation.de/China.html|title=China: Provinces, Prefectures, Counties, Cities, Districts, Townships, Urban Areas - Population Statistics in Maps and Charts|website=www.citypopulation.de|access-date=2019-06-18}}</ref>\n\n=== Urban Population ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|Legend:\n<sup>\u235f</sup> [[List of national capitals|National Capital City]]\n\n<sup>#</sup> [[National Central City]]\n\n<sup>*</sup> [[List of capitals in China|Provincial Capital City]]\n\n<sup>~</sup> [[Special economic zones of China#List of the SEZs and Open Coastal Cities|Open Coastal City]]\n\n<sup>\u2020</sup> [[Special economic zones of China|Special Economic Zone]]\n|}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n| style=\"background:#ffff99; width:1em\" |\n| [[Direct-administered municipalities of China|Direct-Administered Municipality]]\n|-\n| style=\"background:#E0CEF2; width:1em\" |\n| [[List of capitals in China#List of the Municipalities with Independent Planning Status|Municipality with Independent Planning Status]]\n|-\n| style=\"background:#CEF2E0; width:1em\" |\n| [[Sub-provincial division#Sub-provincial municipalities|Sub-Provincial City]]\n|-\n| style=\"background:#ff9999; width:1em\" |\n| [[Prefecture-level city|Prefecture-Level City]]\n|}\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|+\nTop 50 of the Largest Cities in Mainland China by Population of Urban Area\n!Rank\n![[List of cities in China|City]]\n![[Provinces of China|Province]]\n!Latest Estimate<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://populationstat.com/china/|title=China Population (2020)|website=PopulationStat|access-date=2020-02-28}}</ref>\n![[Sixth National Population Census of the People's Republic of China|2010 Census]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.citypopulation.de/China-UA.html|title=China: Provinces and Major Cities - Population Statistics, Maps, Charts, Weather and Web Information|website=www.citypopulation.de|access-date=2019-06-18}}</ref>\n|-\n|1\n|style=\"text-align:left;background-color:#ffff99\"|[[Shanghai]]<sup>